cs.NI, cs.OS, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper discusses the implementation and tuning of the TCP stack in the Linux kernel, which falls under the categories of network protocols (cs.NI), operating systems (cs.OS), and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses potential security implications of modifying the TCP stack, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of eBPF, which is a technology used for system tracing and performance analysis, falling under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
